722281f-a.text:
Park Ave., east side, north from, but not including East 58th Street. Note the former Anderson Galleries, at the S.E. corner of East 59th Street.
June 11, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

722282f-a.text:
(1)
Park Avenue, east side, from 58th to 59th Streets, seen from across the clearing on the N.W. corner of 58th Street where a twenty-story apartment building will be erected. 485 Park Avenue, built about 1923, replaced two small garages on the N.E. corner of 58th Street. Beyond it on 58th Street may be seen the facade of old Liederkranz Hell, from which the cheese
derived its name.
July 3, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, showing the entire Anderson Galleries building in the northern half of the block. Compara the view of this
block in 1917.
July 3, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The Anderson Galleries, and showing also its East 59th
Street side.
June 11, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

722287f-a.text:
Park Ave., west side, south from and including East 59th Street and showing prominently at the S.W. corner of same, No. 500, the executive offices of the Board of Education. The 20-story structure adjacent to same is an apartment house, No. 480 Park Ave., at the N.W. corner of
East 58th Street.
August 4, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
